<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>AI in Construction | Portfolio</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --ink-black: #0d1b2a;
      --prussian-blue: #1b263b;
      --dusk-blue: #415a77;
      --dusty-denim: #778da9;
      --alabaster-grey: #e0e1dd;
      --white: #f8fafc;
      --shadow: 0 18px 40px rgba(13, 27, 42, 0.16);
      --radius-lg: 24px;
      --radius-md: 18px;
      --radius-sm: 12px;
      --max-width: 1200px;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    html {
      scroll-behavior: smooth;
    }

    body {
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--alabaster-grey) 0%, #eef2f5 100%);
      color: var(--ink-black);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    img {
      max-width: 100%;
      display: block;
      border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    }

    a {
      text-decoration: none;
      color: inherit;
    }

    .container {
      width: min(92%, var(--max-width));
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .site-header {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 1000;
      backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
      background: rgba(224, 225, 221, 0.82);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(27, 38, 59, 0.08);
    }

    .nav {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 1rem 0;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .brand {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
    }

    .nav-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .nav-links a {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--dusk-blue);
      transition: color 0.2s ease;
    }

    .nav-links a:hover,
    .nav-links a:focus {
      color: var(--ink-black);
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
    }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding: 0.45rem 0.85rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(119, 141, 169, 0.18);
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 5vw, 5rem);
      line-height: 1.05;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: var(--ink-black);
    }

    .hero h1 span {
      color: var(--dusk-blue);
    }

    .hero p {
      font-size: 1.08rem;
      max-width: 62ch;
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .hero-actions {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .button,
    .button-secondary {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 0.95rem 1.3rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-weight: 700;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
    }

    .button {
      background: var(--ink-black);
      color: var(--white);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }

    .button-secondary {
      border: 1.5px solid rgba(13, 27, 42, 0.15);
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    }

    .button:hover,
    .button-secondary:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .hero-card {
      background: linear-gradient(145deg, var(--prussian-blue), var(--dusk-blue));
      color: var(--white);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      padding: 2rem;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      min-height: 420px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-between;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .hero-card::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: auto -60px -60px auto;
      width: 180px;
      height: 180px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: rgba(224, 225, 221, 0.12);
    }

    .hero-card h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .hero-card p,
    .hero-card li {
      color: rgba(248, 250, 252, 0.92);
    }

    .stat-list {
      list-style: none;
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .stat-list li {
      padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
      border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    section {
      padding: 4.5rem 0;
    }

    .section-heading {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      max-width: 760px;
    }

    .section-heading .tag {
      color: var(--dusk-blue);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
      display: block;
    }

    .section-heading h2 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 3.2rem);
      line-height: 1.1;
      color: var(--ink-black);
      margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }

    .section-heading p {
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      font-size: 1.02rem;
    }

    .about-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .card {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.58);
      border: 1px solid rgba(27, 38, 59, 0.09);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      padding: 1.6rem;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(13, 27, 42, 0.06);
    }

    .card h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
    }

    .skills {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .skill-pill {
      padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(119, 141, 169, 0.18);
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .news-grid,
    .projects-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .news-card,
    .project-card {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.72), rgba(255,255,255,0.55));
      border: 1px solid rgba(27, 38, 59, 0.08);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(13, 27, 42, 0.06);
      transition: transform 0.22s ease, box-shadow 0.22s ease;
    }

    .news-card:hover,
    .project-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
      box-shadow: 0 18px 30px rgba(13, 27, 42, 0.1);
    }

    .card-image {
      height: 200px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--dusty-denim), var(--dusk-blue));
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      color: var(--white);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .card-content {
      padding: 1.35rem;
    }

    .meta {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--dusk-blue);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    }

    .card-content h3 {
      font-size: 1.22rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
      color: var(--ink-black);
    }

    .card-content p {
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .link-arrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.45rem;
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .cta {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--prussian-blue), var(--ink-black));
      color: var(--white);
      border-radius: 32px;
      padding: 2.5rem;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }

    .cta-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .cta h2 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 3rem);
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
    }

    .cta p {
      color: rgba(248, 250, 252, 0.9);
    }

    .contact-list {
      list-style: none;
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.9rem;
    }

    .contact-list li {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
      padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    }

    footer {
      padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
      color: var(--prussian-blue);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .footer-row {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(27, 38, 59, 0.12);
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .hero-grid,
      .about-grid,
      .cta-grid,
      .news-grid,
      .projects-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .hero-card {
        min-height: auto;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .hero {
        padding-top: 3.5rem;
      }

      .nav {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }

      .nav-links {
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .hero h1 {
        font-size: 2.4rem;
      }

      section {
        padding: 3.5rem 0;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="site-header">
    <div class="container nav">
      <a href="#home" class="brand">JM | AI Construction Portfolio</a>
      <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Main navigation">
        <a href="#about">About Me</a>
        <a href="#news">AI News & Articles</a>
        <a href="#projects">Projects & Assignments</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="hero" id="home">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">University of Kansas | Master’s in Construction Management</span>
          <h1>AI in Construction and <span>Construction Design</span> Portfolio</h1>
          <p>
            Welcome to my portfolio website for the AI in Construction and Construction Design course at the University of Kansas.
            This site highlights my background, curated AI news and articles, and selected projects and assignments completed during the semester.
          </p>
          <p>
            The goal of this portfolio is to show how emerging AI tools, workflows, and design thinking can support better decision-making,
            communication, and innovation in the construction industry.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button" href="#projects">View Projects</a>
            <a class="button-secondary" href="#news">Read AI News</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="hero-card" aria-label="Portfolio overview">
          <div>
            <h2>Website Overview</h2>
            <p>
              This portfolio is organized into three main sections based on the course assignment requirements.
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul class="stat-list">
            <li><strong>About Me:</strong> academic background, interests, and professional focus in construction management.</li>
            <li><strong>AI News & Articles:</strong> recent developments, summaries, and reflections on AI trends affecting construction.</li>
            <li><strong>Projects & Assignments:</strong> featured work from this semester with short descriptions and takeaways.</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <span class="tag">About Me</span>
          <h2>Background, interests, and professional goals</h2>
          <p>
            Use this section to introduce yourself, your construction management experience, your interests in AI,
            and how this course connects to your long-term career goals.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-grid">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Professional Summary</h3>
            <p>
              I am a master’s degree student in Construction Management at the University of Kansas with an interest in how
              artificial intelligence can improve estimating, project delivery, design coordination, and decision-making in the built environment.
            </p>
            <p>
              My coursework and project experience this semester focus on understanding how AI tools can support construction professionals
              through automation, data analysis, planning, and communication.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="card">
            <h3>Skills & Focus Areas</h3>
            <p>
              This section can be customized with the software, workflows, and industry topics you want to emphasize.
            </p>
            <div class="skills">
              <span class="skill-pill">Construction Management</span>
              <span class="skill-pill">AI in Construction</span>
              <span class="skill-pill">Project Planning</span>
              <span class="skill-pill">Construction Design</span>
              <span class="skill-pill">Estimating & Analysis</span>
              <span class="skill-pill">Emerging Technology</span>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="news">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <span class="tag">AI News & Articles</span>
          <h2>Recent AI developments and course-related insights</h2>
          <p>
            Add current articles, news stories, or short summaries that connect AI trends to construction, design, safety,
            productivity, scheduling, robotics, or project management.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-grid">
          <article class="news-card">
            <div class="card-image">Article 01<br />AI for construction planning and scheduling</div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <span class="meta">Recent AI News</span>
              <h3>How AI is reshaping planning workflows</h3>
              <p>
                Replace this text with a short summary of an article discussing how AI tools are helping teams improve planning,
                forecasting, and schedule performance in construction projects.
              </p>
              <a class="link-arrow" href="#">Read Article →</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="news-card">
            <div class="card-image">Article 02<br />Automation, safety, and field technology</div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <span class="meta">Industry Insight</span>
              <h3>AI tools supporting safer job sites</h3>
              <p>
                Replace this with a short reflection on how machine learning, monitoring systems, or predictive analytics could improve jobsite safety.
              </p>
              <a class="link-arrow" href="#">Read Article →</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="news-card">
            <div class="card-image">Article 03<br />Design, data, and decision-making</div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <span class="meta">Course Reflection</span>
              <h3>Why AI matters in construction design</h3>
              <p>
                Replace this with your own course takeaway about how AI can support design coordination, information flow,
                and early-stage decision-making.
              </p>
              <a class="link-arrow" href="#">Read Article →</a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="projects">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <span class="tag">Projects & Assignments</span>
          <h2>Selected work from this semester</h2>
          <p>
            Showcase your best assignments, project summaries, research writeups, presentations, or AI-related experiments from the course.
            Each card can later link to a separate file, PDF, slide deck, or hosted page on Tiiny.host.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="projects-grid">
          <article class="project-card">
            <div class="card-image">Project 01<br />Assignment Preview</div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <span class="meta">Semester Project</span>
              <h3>Project Title Placeholder</h3>
              <p>
                Add a brief summary of the assignment, what problem it explored, which AI methods or concepts were involved,
                and the main result or takeaway.
              </p>
              <a class="link-arrow" href="#">View Project →</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="project-card">
            <div class="card-image">Project 02<br />Research / Analysis</div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <span class="meta">Course Assignment</span>
              <h3>Project Title Placeholder</h3>
              <p>
                Use this card for a report, analysis, benchmark review, construction workflow case study, or another assignment from the semester.
              </p>
              <a class="link-arrow" href="#">View Project →</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="project-card">
            <div class="card-image">Project 03<br />Presentation / Deliverable</div>
            <div class="card-content">
              <span class="meta">Featured Work</span>
              <h3>Project Title Placeholder</h3>
              <p>
                Add a short explanation of the project objective, tools used, and what you learned about AI in construction or construction design.
              </p>
              <a class="link-arrow" href="#">View Project →</a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cta">
          <div class="cta-grid">
            <div>
              <h2>Let’s connect</h2>
              <p>
                Use this section to share your email, LinkedIn, and any other professional contact information relevant to the assignment.
                You can also use it as a simple call-to-action for instructors, classmates, or future employers.
              </p>
            </div>
            <ul class="contact-list">
              <li><strong>Email:</strong> yourname@ku.edu</li>
              <li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> linkedin.com/in/your-profile</li>
              <li><strong>Location:</strong> Kansas / United States</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container footer-row">
      <p>© 2026 J M | AI in Construction and Construction Design Portfolio</p>
      <p>Built for hosting on Tiiny.host</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
